sql:
SELECT name
FROM accommodations
WHERE rating = (SELECT MAX(rating) FROM accommodations);

SELECT capital_name, 
       LENGTH(major_attractions) - LENGTH(REPLACE(major_attractions, ',', '')) + 1 AS attraction_count
FROM capitals;

external_knowledge:
Total cost refers to the sum of booking price and accommodation expenses for each booking; 
Accommodation expenses are the sum of the price per night for all accommodations in a booking; 
Highest to lowest refers to the order in which the total costs are sorted.
